column5: Anyone fished here. The lakes to the south in Quetico are apparently good walleye and bass lakes. Not sure about this one.Any information will be a help. Thanks,Mike
https://www.walleyecentral.com/forums...light=nym+lakeSome results from the search function. Good luck!Post a report when you get back!
I did search and found nothing....probably spelled it wrong...it is three letters!There was the only post with substance...and it was old.

Nym is a smallmouth bass lake, i fished it about twenty years ago, no walleye where caught. i was told that many years ago it was a good walleye lake but the smallmouth eventually took over, it has several cottages on it. There is a one mile portage into the park from Nym.
